Program: Outlook
Title: The Street Children of Kinshasa
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbsky
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
The street children of Kinshasa, accused of witchcraft and cast out by their families. Also, 70-year-old Yuichiro Miura, the oldest person to climb Mount Everest. English journalist Mary Ann Sieghart and Jo Livingstone talk about living with prosopagnosia (face-blindness). Kevin Rolle, the 12-year-old Bahamian university student. Finally, a memorable journey from Iraqi-occupied Kuwait to Saudi Arabia. Show less